# Chapter 14 — The Secret Project

*In an office, a distraction is just a task that someone else thinks is more important than yours. And if you want to hide a shadow, you have to create a much bigger, brighter light to draw the auditor’s eye.*

---

Juan dela Cruz sat at his desk at 10:15 PM. The office was finally empty, except for the hum of the servers and the distant sound of the street traffic in BGC. 

Isabel Reyes had left an hour ago, but the 'Detection Meter' in his vision was still sitting at a precarious 35%. 

```
║  ALERT: DETECTION METER: 35% [|||      ] ║
║  Status: [ UNDER INVESTIGATION ]         ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════╝
```

"Rodel," Juan whispered. "Open the Skyfall logs again. The unedited ones."

The shadow emerged, its dark hands flickering over the keyboard. 

*"The logs are dangerous, boss,"* Rodel warned. *"If Isabel sees us accessing these, the meter will hit 100% instantly."*

"She won't see us. Because we're not just going to read them. We're going to use them to trigger a 'System Error' on the 14th floor."

Juan leaned in. He had found something in the logs during the Q3 dungeon—a project code-named *'Aethelgard'*. It wasn't a client project. it was an internal fund-management system used by the S-Rank executives. 

And according to the logs, *Aethelgard* had a critical vulnerability that had been 'patched' with the stolen money from the Skyfall migration.

```
╔══════════════════════════════════════════╗
║              ⚠ HIDDEN QUEST ⚠            ║
║                                          ║
║  [ PROJECT AETHELGARD ]                  ║
║  Objective: Leak the vulnerability       ║
║  to a 'Neutral' third party.             ║
║                                          ║
║  REWARD:                                 ║
║  - Detection Meter Reset (-30%)          ║
║  - New Skill: [ ANONYMOUS WHISTLEBLOWER ]║
║                                          ║
║  PENALTY: 14TH FLOOR EXPOSURE            ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════╝
```

"Rodel, package the vulnerability data. Anonymize the source. Use the 'Shadow Proxy' we built during the pitch."

*"And who is the recipient, boss?"*

Juan looked at his notebook. He had a list of the 14th-floor executives. Most were Aldrich’s cronies. But there was one who was known for being a 'Purist'—a man who hated inefficiency and corruption as much as Juan did.

*CEO GABRIEL SORIANO.*

Gabriel was the 'Final Boss' of the company, but he was also the only one who could stop Isabel’s audit if he was busy with something more important.

"Send it to Gabriel’s private 'urgent' inbox," Juan said. "And make sure the 'Bug Report' is so technical that only a Rank-S investigator like Isabel could decipher it."

*"I see, boss,"* Rodel whispered, his dark eyes glowing. *"You're giving her a new dungeon to explore."*

"Exactly. If she’s busy auditing the CEO’s secret project, she won't have time to look under my floorboards."

```
║  STAMINA: 8% [|         ]                ║
║  WARNING: SYSTEM SHUTDOWN IMMINENT       ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════╝
```

The drain was agonizing. Juan felt his consciousness slipping, his body feeling like it was made of lead. He watched as the progress bar for the upload reached 100%.

**[ UPLOAD COMPLETE. ANONYMOUS SOURCE VERIFIED. ]**

Juan slumped over his desk. He didn't have enough stamina to walk to the elevator. He didn't even have enough to call an Uber. 

The darkness of the office began to close in. 

But then, a hand touched his shoulder. 

It wasn't a shadow. It was warm. It was real.

"Juan? Juan, wake up."

He forced his eyes open. Cynthia Ocampo was standing over him, her car keys in her hand. She looked exhausted, but her eyes were full of a strange, fierce light.

"I saw your light was still on," she said. "You’re going to kill yourself, Juan. Or the System is going to kill you."

"I'm... I'm just documenting," Juan managed to say.

Cynthia looked at his screen. The Aethelgard data was already gone, replaced by a generic infrastructure diagram. But she wasn't looking at the screen. She was looking at the way his shadow was still flickering, even in the low light.

"I don't know what you’re playing at, Juan," she whispered. "But the 14th floor is already on fire. I just saw Aldrich being escorted out by security. Something about a 'whistleblower' report."

Juan felt a surge of relief. It had worked.

"Come on," Cynthia said, pulling his arm over her shoulder. "I'm driving you home. You’re no use to me if you’re dead."

```
╔══════════════════════════════════════════╗
║               QUEST CLEAR!               ║
║                                          ║
║  - Detection Meter: 35% → 5%             ║
║  - Exp Gained: 2,000                     ║
║  - New Skill: [ ANONYMOUS WHISTLEBLOWER ]║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════╝
```

As they walked toward the elevator, Juan saw Isabel Reyes standing by the reception desk. She wasn't looking at him. She was staring at her tablet, her face pale. She had just received the *Aethelgard* file.

She looked up at the 14th floor, her eyes full of the hunt.

Juan leaned into Cynthia, letting her support his weight. He had survived another day. He had recruited an ally. And he had turned his greatest threat into his most effective distraction.

The Phoenix was still rising. But the shadows were now controlling the fire.

